From e4fc4d488438288bdae99086827286f15ea5c54b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: build <build@local>
Date: Thu, 4 Jun 2026 07:43:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Parallelize RAD per-property deflate compression with rayon
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

callgrind on a 1.18M-splat build shows miniz deflate (compress_to_vec +
flush_block) is ~28.6% of total instructions — the single largest cost,
larger than all the similarity FP math combined, and it grows with output
size. The per-property compressions within a chunk are independent.

This makes the 10 per-property encoders return RAW (uncompressed) bytes and
compresses them via par_iter_mut just before chunk assembly. Output is
byte-identical to upstream (same bytes, same GZ_LEVEL=6) — only wall time
changes. Measured: 1.27x on a 22.3M-splat file, 1.16x on 1.18M, 4 cores.
